.\" docs/man/meow-generate.1
.TH MEOW-GENERATE 1 "2025-08-08" "meowg1k" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
meow-generate \- generate any content based on input — code, text, or docs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B meow generate
[\fIflags\fR] [\fIarguments...\fR]
.br
.B meow g
[\fIflags\fR] [\fIarguments...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Send a prompt (and optionally stdin) to an AI model and print the result.
Supports cloud models (Gemini 2.5: Pro & Flash) and local inference (llama.cpp).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-task " " \fINAME\fR
Run a predefined task from config (project or user config).
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-model " " \fINAME\fR
Model name (e.g. \fBgemini-2.5-pro\fR or \fBgemini-2.5-flash\fR). Ignored when \fB--provider=llama\fR.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system\-prompt " " \fITEXT\fR
System prompt (high-level instruction, e.g. "You are a senior Go engineer").
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-user\-prompt " " \fITEXT\fR
User prompt for generation (can be combined with stdin).
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-provider " " \fINAME\fR
LLM provider: \fBgemini\fR (cloud) or \fBllama\fR (local llama.cpp).
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-llama\-base\-url " " \fIURL\fR
Base URL for llama.cpp (required when \fB--provider=llama\fR).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show command help.
.SH PROVIDERS
.TP
.B gemini  (default)
Google Gemini 2.5 (Pro/Flash). Requires \fBMEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY\fR in environment.
.TP
.B llama
Local \fBllama.cpp\fR HTTP server. The model is chosen by the server; \fB--model\fR is ignored.
Use \fB--llama-base-url\fR to connect.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration files are read with the following precedence:
.IP "1." 3
Project: \fB./.meowg1k/config.yaml\fR
.IP "2."
User: \fB~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml\fR
.PP
Flags always override configuration values.
.SH EXAMPLES
Explain Go code (Gemini Pro):
.br
.B cat main.go | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-pro \-p "Explain this code"
.PP
Refactor for performance (Gemini Flash):
.br
.B cat component.js | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-flash \-p "Refactor for performance"
.PP
Strict system prompt for review:
.br
.B cat utils.go | meow g \-m gemini\-2.5\-pro \-s "You are a senior Go engineer focusing on concurrency and safety" \-p "Review this for race conditions"
.PP
Use local llama.cpp:
.br
.B meow g \-P llama \-u http://127.0.0.1:8080 \-p "Summarize this code"
.PP
Run a task from config (Gemini):
.br
.B cat app.py | meow g \-t pytest\-gemini
.PP
Run a task from config (llama.cpp):
.br
.B cat main.rs | meow g \-t refactor\-llama
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for the Gemini provider.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR meow (1),
.BR meow\-version (1),
.BR meow\-config (5),
.BR meow\-security (7)
